#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: description
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to preview blog posts locally: one-command container-based Jekyll serve with auto-detection of changed posts and deep-linking.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Yaml Front Matter Hash Value: name
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "building-blog"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Building Blog Posts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Supported Platforms"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This workflow is supported on Linux, macOS, and Windows through WSL2.\n"
"Native Windows shells (PowerShell, CMD, Git Bash) are not supported.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Quick Start"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Run the full preview pipeline in one command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "just blog-preview\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "Or directly:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "bash blog-preview.sh\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "How It Works"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "The script uses marker files to track state across runs:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"`.blog-preview-last-run` — timestamp of the last preview run.\n"
"Used to detect recently changed posts and open the right URL.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "`.blog-preview.lock` — directory-based lock to prevent concurrent runs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Both files are gitignored. Delete `.blog-preview-last-run` to reset\n"
"change detection.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "What the Script Does"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "Step 1 — Environment Detection"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Detects the container runtime (`podman` or `docker`), SELinux state\n"
"(sets `:z` volume flag if needed), and browser command (`xdg-open`,\n"
"`open`, or `wslview`).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:48
#, no-wrap
msgid "Step 2 — Container Management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Builds a Jekyll image from `jekyll-container/Dockerfile` in this repo\n"
"and starts a preview container. If a healthy container is already\n"
"running from a previous invocation, it is reused without restart.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:60
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The container runs with:\n"
"* `--future` — always included so posts with future dates are visible\n"
"* `--livereload` — browser auto-refreshes on file changes (port 35729)\n"
"* `--incremental` — only rebuilds changed pages\n"
"* `_noguides_config.yml` — excludes guides for fast builds (~10s)\n"
"* Named volume `quarkus-blog-jekyll-bundles` — persists gems across restarts\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "Step 3 — Detect and Open"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "The script auto-detects what you were working on and opens the right page:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:71
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Changed posts | Preview URLs |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| 1 post | `/blog/` (listing) + `/blog/<slug>/` (deep-link) |\n"
"| 2–4 posts | `/blog/` (listing) + a tab for each post |\n"
"| 5+ posts | `/blog/` (listing only), unless git narrows it (see below) |\n"
"| No changes | `/blog/` (listing only) |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:76
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When the timestamp marker is stale and detects 5+ changed posts, the\n"
"script cross-references with git to find posts you actually added or\n"
"modified. If the intersection is smaller (1–4 posts), those are used\n"
"instead and deep links open as in the 1-post or 2–4-post cases above.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:79
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The slug is derived from the filename: strip the `YYYY-MM-DD-` prefix\n"
"and the file extension (`.adoc`, `.asciidoc`, or `.md`).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "Iteration Loop"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "Edit .adoc → save → Jekyll auto-rebuilds → browser auto-refreshes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:88
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The container stays running. LiveReload on port 35729 triggers the\n"
"browser refresh automatically — no manual reload needed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `--future` Flag"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:95
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The `--future` flag is always included because blog contributors\n"
"typically work on posts with today's or a future publication date.\n"
"Without this flag, Jekyll silently excludes future-dated posts from\n"
"the generated site.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:101
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Port 4000 or 35729 already in use** — Another process is using the\n"
"preview ports. Stop the existing container:\n"
"`podman rm -f quarkus-blog-preview` (or `docker`).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:105
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**`Failed to delete .cache/` or permission errors** — Rootless Podman\n"
"UID mapping. Fix: `podman unshare rm -rf .cache/`. With Docker:\n"
"`rm -rf .cache/`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:109
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Volume mount errors on macOS/Ubuntu** — SELinux `:z` flag applied\n"
"on a system without SELinux. The script detects this automatically;\n"
"if it persists, check `getenforce` output.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:112
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Preview shows stale content** — Jekyll's `--incremental` mode can\n"
"sometimes miss dependency changes. Restart the container and re-run:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (bash)
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:112
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"podman rm -f quarkus-blog-preview\n"
"just blog-preview\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:120
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Container image build fails** — Check the build log printed by the\n"
"script. To force a rebuild of the local image:\n"
"`podman rmi quarkus-blog-jekyll:local` (or `docker`).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: .agents/skills/building-blog/SKILL.md:123
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Post not appearing** — Check that the file is in `_posts/` with the\n"
"correct `YYYY-MM-DD-slug.adoc` naming and that the front matter `date`\n"
"matches the filename date.\n"
msgstr ""
